description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Dudley / Walsall / Sandwell&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Excellent rates of pay&lt;/strong&gt;£15.85 per hour Inclusive of Holiday pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have several bank positions for Immunisation nurses working on the School Aged Immunisation Programme with an immediate start available.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity to join our school immunisation teams to make a difference to child health in&lt;strong&gt;Dudley / Walsall and Sandwell&lt;/strong&gt;. VUK are the NHS commissioned providers of the childhood flu programme and the school aged immunisation service. As the provider of these programmes VUK are responsible for the delivery of the nasal influenza vaccine to eligible pupils in Dudley, Sandwell and Walsall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our services are primarily delivered on-site in schools for children of primary and secondary age, however, we also deliver these immunisations in community clinic settings. These clinics may be held during evenings, weekends and school holidays. Due to the community nature of our services driving is essential and you must have access to a car.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will be on offered on a bank contract with an immediate start available. The hours of work will be from 0830 until the end of the school day, or the completion of the immunisation session. You must be able to arrive on time and stay until needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking nurses with immunisation experience ideally with a practice nurse, school nurse or community nursing background and an ability to commit to at least two shifts per week. Weekly shifts can be flexible to fit your availability. Due to the specialist nature of the work VUK are offering a very competitive hourly rate, paid mileage and a friendly and supportive working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an RN with access to transport, an interest in child health, and experience in giving immunisations, we would love to hear from you. You will have the opportunity to work both autonomously, and as part of a small team to organise, plan, deliver, and evaluate immunisation and vaccination programmes for this school - based programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require you to have mandatory training in place which should include Safeguarding Children and Adults at level 3 as a minimum, FGM, Prevent and Immunisation Training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to all training being completed or with a completion date set prior to starting. Without this training, you will not be able to undertake this role. We can provide training for any of these areas that are not currently in date, with prior notice. Knowledge of Health and Safety issues is essential.We also require all clinical staff to show evidence of immunity to hepatitis B, and measles, mumps and rubella immunity prior to commencing work with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be substantial access to children; therefore, an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring check will be required and sign up to the update service is part of our requirements. Interviews may be held remotely on Zoom or Teams due COVID-19 social distancing measures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply, please use the Apply Now link below.&lt;/p&gt;
